Class:AEO_0000079.text: A small cavity bounded by an epithelium.

Class:AEO_0000222.text: An anatomical space with no opening to another space or to the exterior.

Class:CARO_0000010.text: Non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions, that is demarcated by anatomical lines or points on the external or internal surfaces of anatomical structures.

Class:CARO_0000055.text: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more portions of tissue of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona-fide boundaries from other distinct structural units of different types.

Class:CL_0000058.text: An immature cartilage-producing cell found in growing cartilage.

Class:CL_0000062.text: A bone-forming cell which secretes an extracellular matrix. Hydroxyapatite crystals are then deposited into the matrix to form bone.

Class:AEO_0000090.text: A strap of predominantly extracellular matrix connecting two bones.

Class:CL_0002320.text: A cell of the supporting or framework tissue of the body, arising chiefly from the embryonic mesoderm and including adipose tissue, cartilage, and bone.

Class:CARO_0000040.text: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

Class:AEO_0000193.text: Organ or organ part that is attached to the body of an organism. For example a limb[GO, modified]. An appendage is an external body part, or natural prolongation, that protrudes from an organism's body, such as a vertebrate's limbs.

Class:AEO_0000125.text: A structure whose morphology or state of differentiation will change during normal development.

Class:AEO_0000131.text: Embronic structure that contains stem cellsr that may contribute to its future development or maintenance or to its future development or maintenance of another tissue.

Class:AEO_0000135.text: A group of neurons, usually outside the CNS, which relay neuronal signals.

Class:CL_0000129.text: A central nervous system macrophage found in the parenchyma of the central nervous system. Marker include CD11b-positive, F4/80-positive, and CD68-positive.

Class:CL_0000526.text: A neuron which conveys sensory information centrally from the periphery.

Class:CL_0000737.text: Muscle cell which has as its direct parts myofilaments organized into sarcomeres.

Class:CL_0000746.text: A myocyte located in the heart. The contractile fiber resembles those of skeletal muscle but are only one third as large in diameter, are richer in sarcoplasm, and contain centrally located instead of peripheral nuclei.

Class:AEO_0000151.text: Mesenchyme whose cells are embedded in obvious amounts fo extracellular matrix.

Class:AEO_0000183.text: A joint connecting two or more bones with cartilage at the bone ends and a synovial membrane that secretes synovial fluid conecting the bones and sealing the synovial cavity.

Class:AEO_0000186.text: The cavity within the body that contains the visceral organs.

Class:CARO_0000005.text: Non-material anatomical entity of three dimensions, that is generated by morphogenetic or other physiologic processes; is surrounded by one or more anatomical structures; contains one or more organism substances or anatomical structures.

Class:AEO_0000199.text: A membranous structure with more than one cell type, one or more of which secretes mucus, that lines body passages which communicate with the exterior.

Class:AEO_0000200.text: An anatomical structure that, as part of its normal physiology, undergoes regeneration. Examples include endometrium and antlers.

Class:CL_0000066.text: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface. The cell has a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.

Class:AEO_0000211.text: The sum of all the anlagen and primordia that will develop into a single functional system.

Class:AEO_0000212.text: The mesenchymal derivative of a somite that will migrate to surround the neural tube and form vertebrae.

Class:AEO_0000215.text: A volume that is mainly bounded but has an opening to another cavity or to the outside.

Class:CL_0000136.text: A fat-storing cell found mostly in the abdominal cavity and subcutaneous tissue of mammals. Fat is usually stored in the form of triglycerides.

Class:CL_0002573.text: A glial cell that ensheathes axons of neuron in the peripheral nervous system and are necessary for their maintainance and function.

Class:CL_0000107.text: A neruon whose cell body is within an autonomic ganglion.

Class:AEO_0001006.text: Excreta are bodily fluids consisting of waste matter, such as sweat or feces, discharged from the body.

Class:AEO_0001009.text: An epithelium that is undergoing proliferation to provide large numbers of neuronal cells.

Class:AEO_0001018.text: A transitional population of migrating mesenchymal cells that derive from somites and that will become muscle cells.

Class:CARO_0000000.text: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

Class:CARO_0000008.text: Non-material anatomical entity of one dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical surface or is a modulation of an anatomical surface.

Class:CARO_0000029.text: Multi-cellular organism that can produce both male and female gametes.

Class:CARO_0000050.text: Sequential hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of the female sex, and then later of the male sex.

Class:CARO_0000063.text: Multi-cellular organism that does not produce gametes.

Class:CARO_0000072.text: Compound organ that contains one or more macroscopic anatomical spaces.

Class:CL_0000000.text: Anatomical structure that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

Class:CL_0000015.text: A germline cell that contributes to the development of the oocyte by transferring cytoplasm directly to oocyte.

Class:CL_0000540.text: The basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. Each neuron consists of a body, an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

Class:CL_0000055.text: A precursor cell with a limited number of potential fates.

Class:CL_0000667.text: An extracellular matrix secreting cell that secretes collagen.

Class:CL_0002371.text: A cell of an organism that does not pass on its genetic material to the organism's offspring (i.e. a non-germ line cell).

Class:CL_0000080.text: A cell which moves among different tissues of the body, via blood, lymph, or other medium.

Class:CL_0000165.text: An endocrine cell that has the specialized function to produce and secrete hormones in response to neuronal signals.

Class:CL_0000187.text: A mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte. This cell has as part of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.

Class:CL_0000414.text: A classification of cells by the number of haploid genome equivalents of their nucleus or nuclei.

Class:CL_0002372.text: A myotube is a multinucleated cells that is formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.
